---
/**
 * context-engineering 0008 · Figure 2 — Module 1 "meaning becomes geometry":
 * phrases plotted as points in a 2-D sketch of meaning-space; auth phrases
 * cluster, billing phrases sit in a different region.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/context-engineering/lessons/0008-embeddings-indexing-and-cost.html.
 * Lives as an .astro component (not inline MDX) because raw inline SVG with
 * kebab-case attributes is unreliable in MDX but is plain HTML in .astro.
 *
 * The "far = unrelated" arrow references the shared #arwR marker (fill #9a2417),
 * which the source declared once in a top-of-body <defs>. The MDX has no such
 * block, so that marker is inlined here.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Phrases plotted as points; similar meanings cluster near each other while unrelated ones sit far away."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="300" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Meaning-space (2-D sketch of a 1536-D space)</text
        >
        <rect
            x="40"
            y="30"
            width="520"
            height="200"
            rx="8"
            fill="#ffffff"
            stroke="#111110"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <!-- cluster A: auth -->
        <circle cx="150" cy="90" r="6" fill="#b5179e"></circle><text
            x="162"
            y="94"
            font-size="9.5"
            fill="#111110">"reset the user token"</text
        >
        <circle cx="180" cy="120" r="6" fill="#b5179e"></circle><text
            x="192"
            y="124"
            font-size="9.5"
            fill="#111110">"log the user out"</text
        >
        <circle cx="135" cy="135" r="6" fill="#b5179e"></circle><text
            x="147"
            y="139"
            font-size="9.5"
            fill="#111110">"revoke the session"</text
        >
        <line x1="150" y1="90" x2="180" y2="120" stroke="#b5179e" stroke-dasharray="3 2"></line>
        <text x="120" y="70" font-size="9" font-style="italic" fill="#b5179e"
            >near = similar meaning</text
        >
        <!-- cluster B: billing -->
        <circle cx="450" cy="170" r="6" fill="#2f5d3a"></circle><text
            x="338"
            y="174"
            text-anchor="end"
            font-size="9.5"
            fill="#111110">"charge the credit card"</text
        >
        <circle cx="480" cy="195" r="6" fill="#2f5d3a"></circle><text
            x="368"
            y="199"
            text-anchor="end"
            font-size="9.5"
            fill="#111110">"issue a refund"</text
        >
        <text x="470" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-style="italic" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >a different region</text
        >
        <!-- distance arrow -->
        <line
            x1="180"
            y1="120"
            x2="450"
            y2="170"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-dasharray="5 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <text x="315" y="135" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >far = unrelated</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The embedding model learned to place "log the user out" beside "revoke the session" even
        though they share no keywords — that's why semantic search beats keyword match for
        paraphrase, and why the metric we use is <em>distance</em>, not string overlap.<sup
            ><a href="#s3" id="r3">3</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
